Gift to Kim Jong Il from Foreign Ministry Delegation of Myanmar 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 17 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the delegation of the Foreign Ministry of Myanmar on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was conveyed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Monday by Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs U Kyaw Thu who is heading the delegation.

Plunder of Fur-seals by Japanese Imperialists in Tok Islet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 17 (KCNA) -- The Japanese imperialists had captured fur-seals in Tok Islet at random during their occupation of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Tok Islet in the East Sea of Korea is rich in marine resources and famous for the habitat of fur-seals from long ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Japanese imperialists, who had been covetous of the islet, concocted the "notification of the Shimane Prefecture" on attaching it to the prefecture in February 1905. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@After then Japanese reactionaries organized the "Takeshima (Tok Islet) Fishing Joint Venture Company" to capture fur-seals in earnest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@They hunted over 100 fur-seals on the very day of test operation of the company in June 1905 and over 1,000 fur-seals by September that year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The fact clearly discloses how deceptive and hypocritical the "protection of fur-seal resources" and the "proper capture" advocated by the Japanese imperialists were. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@At that time they "stipulated" that the annual capture of fur-seals in Tok Islet should not go beyond the limit of 600 heads under the pretext of "preventing the random capture".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@But Japanese fishing companies, which were engrossed in money-making, wantonly violated the "stipulations" from the first year under the patronage of the government, and raised the amount of fur-seal catch from 600 to 1,500 heads next year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The amount of fur-seal catch grew year after year, reaching more than 2,000 heads in 1907. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@This is also a curtailed number. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Owing to the random hunting of fur-seals by the Japanese imperialists, fur-seals came to diminish in number in Tok islet. Now it is hard to see fur-seals there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Japanese imperialists are the heinous criminals who illegally seized the islet, inalienable territory of Korea, and plundered her of the precious resources. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Japanese authorities should be responsible for the pillage of the resources in Tok Islet in the past and apologize and compensate for it.    
�@

Fifth National Ssirum Tournament for Grand Bull Prize Opened 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 17 (KCNA) -- The Fifth National Ssirum (Korean wrestling) Tournament for Grand Bull Prize started at the Ssirum Ground on the Rungra Island in Pyongyang on September 17. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participated there are the players including Son Kwang Guk and Pak Chun Min of Pyongyang City and Ri Jo Won of North Phyongan Province who proved successful at the third and fourth national tournaments, and many new players. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The rankings of the teams are to be decided through the game results of body-weight grades without team event. It differs from the previous ones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the result of each player has a decisive influence on the ranking of his team, matches were tough from the beginning. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Spectators did not stint their cheers whenever players defeated their opponents by employing various techniques. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is most interest in the tournament is the catch-weight ssirum event. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The finals of catch-weight ssirum event will be held on September 19.

Rodong Sinmun on Programme for Korea's Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 17 (KCNA) -- The June 15 joint declaration serves as an action programme common to the nation and a banner of victory that all Koreans should always hold fast to in the movement for national reunification at present, says Rodong Sinmun today in a by-lined article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint declaration elucidates the fundamental principles which call on the Koreans responsible for solving the question of national reunification to independently settle it by their concerted efforts, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea of "By our nation itself" enshrined in the declaration is based on the principle of national independence. Only when this principle of independence, the principle calling for resolutely standing against outsiders' domination and intervention, flunkeyism and dependence on outsiders, is adhered to, is it possible for the Korean nation to successfully achieve the cause of national reunification in keeping with its demand and interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said idea presupposes the great unity of the entire nation. Without this unity for strengthening the driving force for national reunification, it is hard to expect victory in the cause of national reunification accompanied by a fierce struggle against the anti-reunification forces. The great unity of the entire nation constitutes powerful strength for shaping the nation's destiny independently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea of "By our nation itself" is basically required for achieving the above-said unity. Therefore, differences in ideology, ism, political view, religious belief, classes and strata should not be absolutized in the matter of achieving the great national unity in the above-said idea. When primary consideration is given to the destiny of the nation and the reunification of the country, its common interests, is put above anything else, such differences can neither be problematic nor be obstructive to achieving the great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint declaration also comprehensively indicates the tasks and ways for realizing national reconciliation and unity and reunifying the country as it calls for solving humanitarian matters between the north and the south of Korea, developing the nation's economy in a balanced way through their economic cooperation and building confidence between the two sides through brisk cooperation and exchange in the social, cultural, sports, health and environmental and various other fields.

World People Advocating Independence Called upon to Unite 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 17 (KCNA) -- The slogan "The world people advocating independence, unite!" put up by President Kim Il Sung serves as a basic guarantee for victoriously advancing the human cause of independence despite any obstructive moves of the imperialists and as a banner of international solidarity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The human desire for independence is now growing stronger as the days go by and it has become an irresistible trend of the times for the popular masses to struggle for advancing the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is possible to isolate and weaken the imperialist and hegemonic forces and further strengthen the anti-imperialist and independent forces only when all the revolutionary countries and progressives in the world desirous of independence achieve unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said slogan serves as a basic guarantee for the victory of the human cause of independence because it indicates a clear way of strengthening the driving force for carrying out the human cause of independence. The world people desirous of independence are the driving force for accomplishing the human cause of independence. Only when the world people firmly unite and cooperate with one another under the banner of independence, is it possible to increase the force for independence and surely frustrate any move of the counter-revolutionary forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international slogan calling on the world people advocating independence to unite reflects the common aspiration of all the world people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The world people advocating independence should counter the imperialists' moves for division and alienation and strategy for destroying them one by one with the strategy of unity and solidarity. Herein lies the key to winning a victory in the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the world progressives firmly unite and cooperate with one another under the banner of independence, the moves of the imperialist and reactionary forces for domination are bound to go bust and the cause of global independence is sure to win one victory after another.

DPRK's Birthday Celebrated in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 17 (KCNA) -- Receptions were given and friendly meetings, photo exhibitions and film shows held at the DPRK missions in Vietnam, Syria, Malaysia, Cambodia, Indonesia, Thailand, Switzerland, Germany, France, Austria, Bulgaria, Egypt, Guinea, Equatorial Guinea, Democratic Congo, Libya, South Africa, Brazil and Mexico and at the DPRK permanent mission at the UN Secretariat and international organizations in Geneva during the period from September 4 to 7 on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the venues of the functions were works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos showing their immortal feats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Addresses and speeches were made at the functions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants in the film shows watched such Korean films as "The Rivers and Mountains of the Country Being Face-lifted under the Leadership of the Great General" and "The 55th Founding Anniversary of the DPRK".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, photo exhibitions were held by the Culture and Art Council of Abuja City, Nigeria and the Laos-Korea Tin Company and film shows by the Grodekov Far East State Museum in Khabarovsk and some companies of Russia, the Indonesia-Korea Association for Friendship and Cultural Exchange and a Thai company between September 6 and 11 on the above-said occasion.

Inheritance of Spirit of Democratic Martyrs Urged in South Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 17 (KCNA) -- South Korean political parties and civic and public organizations reportedly formed "the Committee of Functions for All-People Memorial Services for National and Democratic Martyrs and Victims" at the meeting room of the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions in Seoul on September 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers at the inaugural ceremony called for dynamically waging a struggle against the conclusion of "the Free Trade Agreement" and for the abolition of part-time jobs and repeal of the "National Security Law" by inheriting the spirit of democratic martyrs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the spirit of martyrs could not be inherited without closing the history of national division, they urged all the people to pool strength and wage more daringly the struggle for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A declaration of the formation was read out before the action program of the committee was made public at the inaugural ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony was preceded by a symposium on the theme "Orientation and tasks for remembering the national and democratic martyrs and inheriting their spirit" which involved different organizations.

Kim Il Sung's Reminiscences Introduced in Britain
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 17 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of Songun Policy posted "A Written Warranty for a Good Citizen" from Vol. 5 of Part 1 the Anti-Japanese Revolution of President Kim Il Sung's reminiscences "With the Century" on its Internet homepage on Sept. 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage carried a photograph of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk defending the command of the revolution with her life.

Kye Sun Hui conquista cuatro veces titulo de campeona mundial de judo
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 17 de septiembre (ATCC) -- La judoka coreana Kye Sun Hui gano la medalla de oro en la categoria de 57 kg del Campeonato Mundial de Judo de 2007 efectuado en Rio de Janeiro de Brasil. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En este certamen, Kye vencio con capacidad aplastante a todas las rivales. En particular, en la final, gano por ippong a la judoka espanola a los 65 segundos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi fue como la campeona Kye, laureada con el Premio Kim Il Sung, Heroina del Trabajo y Deportista del Pueblo, llego a mantener sucesivamente a partir de 2001 la posicion de "Reina mundial de judo".

Kim Jong Il recibe presente de delegacion de Myanmar
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 17 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio presente que le dirigiera la delegacion del Ministerio de Relaciones Exteriores de la Union de Myanmar presidida por el viceministro U Kyaw Thu de visita en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El jefe de la delegacion lo entrego el dia 17 al presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam.
